<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-11-16T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-11-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.6362/33: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hofer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-11-16T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">November 16,
                                        1927—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 5:50
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>176. Ambassador’s telegram 168, November 2, 4 p.m. Chamber of Deputies
                            passed coal bill substantially as reported by joint committee late
                            yesterday after short discussion. Bill expected to be sent promptly to
                            the Senate.</p>
                        <p>[Paraphrase.] Seibert says that there is little hope for effective
                            modifications since prestige of Government and Minister of Finance, who
                            has suffered much embarrassment by protests, is involved if Congress
                            does not promptly approve bill. [End paraphrase.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hofer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>